Perfect — here’s one example you can paste directly into a bot setup so it shows up clearly in both **Discord embed** and **Slack block** formats.

---

### **Discord Embed Example**  *(for `!crisis-respond`)*

```json
{
  "embeds": [{
    "title": "Suicidal Crisis Support Message",
    "description": "I'm really sorry you're feeling like this. You don't have to face it alone.\n\n🇺🇸 **In the U.S.:** Call or text **988** (Suicide and Crisis Lifeline, free 24/7).\n🌍 **Outside the U.S.:** Visit **findahelpline.com** to locate international hotlines.\n\nYou're not alone, and help is available right now.",
    "color": 16098851,
    "footer": {
      "text": "Moderator quick‑response | Keep tone calm, brief, and factual."
    }
  }]
}
```

### **Slack Block Example**  *(for `/crisis-respond`)*

```json
{
  "blocks": [
    {
      "type": "section",
      "text": {
        "type": "mrkdwn",
        "text": "*Suicidal Crisis Support Message*\n\nI'm really sorry you're feeling like this. You don't have to face it alone.\n\n🇺🇸 *In the U.S.:* Call or text *988* (Suicide and Crisis Lifeline, 24/7 free and confidential).\n🌍 *Outside the U.S.:* Visit *findahelpline.com* for global hotlines."
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "context",
      "elements": [
        {
          "type": "mrkdwn",
          "text": "Moderator quick‑response | Deliver calmly, then connect to real‑time human help."
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
```

Both examples keep the message short, empathetic, and action‑oriented while making hotline links instantly visible.  
